<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Bayern Munich winger Leroy Sane has been ruled out of action for at least the next two matches with a knee injury.</p>

<p>The German international missed almost the entire 2019-20 campaign for former club Manchester City following knee surgery after tearing a cruciate ligament in the 2019 Community Shield win over Liverpool. </p>

<p>And Bayern coach Hansi Flick revealed on Tuesday that the 24-year-old's new problem is on the same knee.</p>

<p>Bayern Munich will be without winger Leroy Sane for at least the next two matches</p>

<p>Sane's injury means he will miss Wednesday's Super Cup showdown with Borussia Dortmund</p>

<p>It means Sane will miss Bayern's Super Cup showdown with Borussia Dortmund on Wednesday and Sunday's Bundesliga clash with Hertha Berlin.</p>

<p>Sane could also possibly be out of the rescheduled German Cup first-round match against Duren on October 15.</p>

<p>'Leroy is out. Hopefully he will be back after the international break,' Flick said.</p>

<p>'He's got a capsule injury in his knee.'   </p>

<p>Germany winger Sane joined Bayern on a five-year deal from Manchester City in July</p>

<p>Sane, who played for 73 minutes in Bayern’s 4-1 defeat by Hoffenheim on Sunday, which ended a 32-game unbeaten run, is also likely to miss Germany's Nations Cup matches against Ukraine on October 10 and Switzerland three days later.</p>

<p>Sane joined Bayern from City after putting his name to a five-year contract in July.</p>

<p>He has scored one goal and contributed two assists in his first three appearances for the German champions.</p>

<p>Flick also revealed defender David Alaba faces a late fitness test for Wednesday's meeting with Dortmund due to a muscle problem.</p>
